data.title: Enock
data.description:
Although born with spina bifida and paralyzed from the waist down, Enock Glidden​ always held on to a lifelong dream of climbing Yosemite’s El Cap. This film shares the story of how he made the seemingly impossible feat a reality. His journey to the top of El Capitan began with support from the adaptive climbing organization Paradox Sports​ in a climbing gym. We want to help Paradox open doors for climbers of all abilities and are teaming up with them to help bring adaptive climbing techniques to gyms across the U.S.

Learn more here: https://www.thenorthface.com/paradoxsports

Director/Producer: Craig Muderlak, Muderlak Art

Music: 
'Cinematic Piano Background' - Josh Kramer
'Yearning Sentimental Background' - Josh Kramer
'All This Time' - Dan Phillipson
'Increase' - Craig Muderlak
'My Time With You' - Ben Beini
'I Would Have' - Craig Muderlak

data.title: NZ ROADTRIP: RIDING THE GOOD VIBES, Part 1
data.description: We packed our bags, hopped on a plane to the Land Of The Long White Cloud and hit the road. Ernest, our Kombi took us on a journey through rolling hills, fields of green, prehistoric forests filled with enormous ferns, lakes and quaint little towns. We enjoyed candy coloured sunsets and crisp offshore winds, glistening ocean water and perfect afternoon slides. There were lost of laughs, cuddles and late night girl talk - memories were made that will last a lifetime.

data.title: Billabong Surf Capsule Summer 2015
data.description: From treasured archives to modern day salty moments, this season’s Surf Capsule is in full Billabong celebratory spirit. With uninterrupted daydreams of times way back, this meant-to-be-wet collection is all about the sweet side of surfing. For beautiful moments on an epic wave where there’s a dance and a touch of rootsy romanticism, this season’s collection is made with love for the girl who still gets butterflies when she slips on her suit and rubs wax on her board. From classic colorblocking to our sunbaked Heritage print, this season’s soul food is salt water and pure stoke.

data.title: BILLABONG Barbados Summer 2015
data.description: A beautiful moment on a sweet wave, sea glazed eyes peeking at a shoreline of perfect palm trees and silky white sand. Life is a quest to find my own rhythm. Surfing, music, freedom, ocean. These are the notes that I play. Adventure is the beat. Barbados is the canvas. I follow the groove of the locals, Cherry Tree to Soupbowl, drinking in the island life. Cropover festival fills the island with the scent of Bajan cuisine and the sound of steel drums. I express myself through Calypso. It’s the lust for what is around the bend that compels me, the rich Bajan culture that keeps me. A lifetime of dreams fulfilled with it’s perfect wave. Nothing else is need. Freedom found.

data.title: The Road Trip Life
data.description:
You know that dream from high school? The one when you grab your best friends, get a dirty old camper, fill it with surfboards and just take off? Your only care in the world is the coast and your car, and as the days pile up so does the fun.

Creed McTaggart and Dave Rastovich lived out that dream this fall. They surfed, they hiked, they fixed flat tires and sat around campfires. They stopped at funny stores in funky towns, surfed sharky coves and laughed every step of the way.

It was the epitome of the dream, complete with original music written and performed by Rasta.

data.title: BILLABONG: A BIKINI KINDA LIFE
data.description:
A string around her waist, a strap over her shoulder. Her bikini is her second skin. Where she goes, it goes. Sheʼs a wanderer, an explorer, a sun chaser, a wave racer. A thrill seeker, a summer dreamer, a local babe with a worldly spirit. Red sand, white sand, black sand, pink. Deep blue, cobalt, turquoise, green; colours
that provide the backdrop to her life. Summer is in her blood. She belongs to the salt and the salt belongs to her.
She lives #abikinikindalife. And she always wears Billabong.
